        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 15 at 5:01AM EDT by NWS Raleigh NC</headline>
        <description>At 500 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Pope AFB, or near Fort Bragg, moving east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Fayetteville, Fort Bragg, Godwin, Pope AFB, Spring Lake, Eastover,
Stedman, Wade, Falcon, and Vander.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
